  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Pizza oven down during service? Same-day commercial repair:</span><a href="tel:+14243250520" class="phone-lg">(424) 325-0520</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap"><div class="hero-grid"><div class="hero-text"><div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/commercial/">Commercial</a> › Pizza Oven Repair</div><h1>Commercial Pizza Oven Repair in Los Angeles</h1><p class="lede">Conveyor belt pizza ovens (Lincoln Impinger, Middleby Marshall PS/WOW), deck pizza ovens (Bakers Pride Y-600, Blodgett 1048/1060, Marsal SD, legacy Peerless), wood-fired artisan ovens (Wood Stone Mt Adams + Fire Deck + Bistro, Forno Bravo Modena + Napolino + Professionale, Marra Forni rotator), and brick-lined specialty ovens, our techs cover the full commercial pizza oven lineup across LA, Orange County, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. CARB compliant; LA Neapolitan + chain pizza specialists; $120 diagnostic waived with repair.</p><div class="hero-cta"><a href="tel:+14243250520" class="btn btn-primary">Call (424) 325-0520</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div><ul class="hero-facts"><li><b>Three pizza-oven categories</b>, conveyor, deck, wood-fired, all covered in-house</li><li><b>LA Neapolitan pizza cluster specialists</b>, Pizzana, Mozza, Bestia, Mother Dough, Jon & Vinny's, 800 Degrees, Gjelina</li><li><b>Chain pizza franchise coverage</b>, Domino's + Pizza Hut + Papa John's + Little Caesars Middleby Marshall/Lincoln installations</li><li><b>CARB + LADBS compliant</b>, California commercial gas + wood-fired LADBS venting work</li></ul></div><aside class="hero-aside"><div class="aside-card"><h3>Talk to a local branch</h3><a href="tel:+13238704790" class="branch"><b>West Hollywood</b><span>(323) 870-4790</span></a><a href="tel:+14243250520" class="branch"><b>Los Angeles</b><span>(424) 325-0520</span></a><a href="tel:+14242080228" class="branch"><b>Thousand Oaks</b><span>(424) 208-0228</span></a><a href="tel:+16263764458" class="branch"><b>Pasadena</b><span>(626) 376-4458</span></a><a href="tel:+12134019019" class="branch"><b>Irvine</b><span>(213) 401-9019</span></a></div></aside></div></div></section>

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS Licensed #A49573</span><span>EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410</span><span>Same-day · 5 SoCal counties</span><span>$120 commercial diagnostic · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>LA pizza restaurant cluster, from Neapolitan artisan to chain franchise</h2>
    <p>Los Angeles runs one of the most diverse commercial pizza restaurant clusters in the United States. The market spans from Michelin-recommended Neapolitan artisan operations (Pizzana West Hollywood + Brentwood, Mozza Hancock Park, Bestia Arts District, Jon & Vinny's, Mother Dough Los Feliz, L'Antica Pizzeria da Michele Hollywood, 800 Degrees Neapolitan, Gjelina Venice) through mid-market independent pizza shops and casual-dining concepts into the chain franchise segment (Domino's 100-plus LA locations, Pizza Hut, Papa John's, Little Caesars, Marco's Pizza, Blaze Pizza, MOD Pizza, Pieology). Each segment specifies different pizza oven technology; our service coverage spans all three.</p>
    <p>At the Neapolitan artisan end, wood-fired ovens dominate, Wood Stone (Bellingham WA) and Forno Bravo (Carmel Valley CA) are the primary manufacturers serving LA's Neapolitan-certified kitchens. At the mid-market end, deck pizza ovens dominate, Bakers Pride Y-600 is the LA artisan-plus-casual standard; Blodgett 1048 single-deck and 1060 double-deck are common at higher-volume independent operations; Marsal SD series brick-lined specialty ovens appear at Italian-heritage restaurants wanting traditional deck cooking with brick-fired flavor character. At the chain franchise end, conveyor belt ovens dominate, Middleby Marshall PS series is the OEM standard across most major chain pizza franchises nationwide; Lincoln Impinger offers the Welbilt-Ali alternative conveyor technology.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Deck pizza ovens, artisan to mid-volume standard</h2>
    <p>Deck pizza ovens cook pizza on stationary refractory decks at high temperatures (700–900°F), delivering the char and crust character that defines Neapolitan-style pizza. Common across LA artisan and mid-volume independent operations.</p>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Bakers Pride Y-600, LA artisan standard</h3><p>LA's most-installed deck pizza oven across Neapolitan and artisan pizza restaurants. Middleby Corporation since 1999. Y-600 is gas-fired flagship deck; GP series is value-tier gas; DS is cyclone convection. See our dedicated <a href="/brands/bakers-pride-pizza-oven-repair/">Bakers Pride pizza oven repair page</a>.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Blodgett 1048 / 1060, Neapolitan deck</h3><p>Blodgett 1048 single-deck and 1060 double-deck pizza ovens. Common across LA Neapolitan-concept operations (Pizzana, Bestia, Gjelina). Cluster 07 covers Blodgett; see <a href="/brands/blodgett-oven-repair/">Blodgett oven repair page</a>.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Marsal SD + MB series, brick-lined specialty</h3><p>Brick-lined deck pizza ovens (SD series gas, MB series gas or wood-fired hybrid). Independent family-owned Brooklyn NY since 1945. Common at LA Italian-heritage restaurants wanting traditional brick-oven flavor character. Service covered via service-hub dispatch.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Peerless, legacy deck (discontinued)</h3><p>Peerless pizza ovens are an older legacy brand with installations still in service at long-tenure LA pizza operations. Brand appears to be discontinued; parts increasingly scarce. Service available for existing installations; honest repair-vs-replace guidance on 20-plus-year units.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Conveyor pizza ovens, chain franchise and high-volume standard</h2>
    <p>Conveyor belt pizza ovens cook pizza continuously on a moving belt through a heated chamber, delivering throughput that deck ovens can't match. Chain pizza franchises universally spec conveyor ovens for their LA operations because the throughput profile matches delivery-focused franchise operations.</p>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Middleby Marshall PS + WOW, chain pizza OEM</h3><p>The chain-pizza OEM standard across Domino's, Pizza Hut, Papa John's, Little Caesars, and other major pizza franchises nationwide. PS200/220/350/360/536/540/555/570 series conveyors; WOW oven is the high-volume current-gen with bi-directional air-flow. See our dedicated <a href="/brands/middleby-marshall-pizza-oven-repair/">Middleby Marshall pizza oven repair page</a>.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Lincoln Impinger, Welbilt/Ali conveyor</h3><p>Lincoln Impinger signature air-flow conveyor technology. 1100 countertop, 1600/1620 mid-size, 2500/2501 full-size, 3000 series high-volume. Welbilt → Ali Group July 2022. Common at chain franchise operations that didn't specify Middleby Marshall. See <a href="/brands/lincoln-pizza-oven-repair/">Lincoln Impinger pizza oven repair page</a>.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>TurboChef Fire, stone-hearth rapid-cook</h3><p>TurboChef Fire model is a stone-hearth pizza variant of the rapid-cook oven line. Delivers Neapolitan-style char in 90-second cycles. Covered in cluster 07 via <a href="/brands/turbochef-rapid-cook-oven-repair/">TurboChef rapid-cook oven repair page</a>.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Wood-fired pizza ovens, LA Neapolitan artisan cluster</h2>
    <p>Wood-fired ovens define the Neapolitan-certified pizza cluster in LA. Two primary manufacturers, Wood Stone (Bellingham Washington) and Forno Bravo (Carmel Valley California), deliver the wood-fired and hybrid wood-plus-gas technology that Neapolitan-style pizza operations specify. Italian-heritage rotator and artisan brands (Marra Forni, Moretti Forni, Valoriani via Mugnaini distributor) appear in specific installations.</p>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Wood Stone, Bellingham WA hybrid</h3><p>LA Neapolitan-certified pizza cluster standard. Mt Adams hybrid deck, Fire Deck deck ovens, Bistro smaller deck, Plancha open-fired, Stratos rotating deck. Hybrid wood-plus-gas technology specialty. Independent family-owned since 1989. See <a href="/brands/wood-stone-pizza-oven-repair/">Wood Stone pizza oven repair page</a>.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Forno Bravo, Carmel Valley CA California manufacturer</h3><p>California local manufacturer (Monterey County). Modena commercial, Napolino smaller commercial, Professionale flagship artisan, Vesuvio high-capacity, Roma modular. Italian-style wood-fired specialty. Independent family-owned since 2003. California parts-chain advantage (same corridor logic as Imperial Corona + American Range Cypress). See <a href="/brands/forno-bravo-pizza-oven-repair/">Forno Bravo pizza oven repair page</a>.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Marra Forni, Italian-heritage rotator</h3><p>Italian-heritage rotator and brick pizza oven specialty. Beltsville MD US-manufactured Italian design. Service available via service-hub dispatch; mention-only on our brand coverage map.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Mugnaini / Valoriani, Italian premium distributor</h3><p>Mugnaini is the Santa Clara California distributor for Valoriani Italian-made wood-fired ovens. NorCal-based distribution, Italian manufacturing. Service for LA-installed Valoriani units available via service-hub dispatch.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>LA Neapolitan-certified pizza kitchen cluster</h2>
    <p>Los Angeles has one of the densest Neapolitan-certified pizza kitchen clusters in the United States. Neapolitan certification (AVPN, Associazione Verace Pizza Napoletana, and VPN Americas) specifies wood-fired cooking, specific dough preparation standards, and cooking-time thresholds that only high-temperature wood-fired ovens can meet. Key LA operations in the cluster:</p>
    <ul class="check-list">
      <li><b>Pizzana</b> (West Hollywood, Brentwood, Hancock Park), Blodgett 1060 deck + Wood Stone hybrid installations</li>
      <li><b>Mozza</b> (Hancock Park), Italian-concept pizza with Blodgett deck standard</li>
      <li><b>Bestia</b> (Arts District), Italian concept; Blodgett 1048/1060 standard</li>
      <li><b>Jon & Vinny's</b>, LA Italian-concept pizza + pasta</li>
      <li><b>Mother Dough</b> (Los Feliz), Wood Stone wood-fired Neapolitan</li>
      <li><b>L'Antica Pizzeria da Michele</b> (Hollywood), Naples-origin heritage restaurant expanded to LA</li>
      <li><b>800 Degrees Pizza</b>, fast-casual Neapolitan, Wood Stone installations</li>
      <li><b>Gjelina</b> (Venice), Abbot Kinney Italian concept including pizza program</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Service at these operations has specific characteristics: emergency response timing matters because dinner-service pizza-oven failures have immediate revenue impact (Neapolitan operations running at $4-6 per pie at 200+ covers per night); documentation for Neapolitan certification compliance sometimes required; operator-expectation of deep brand-specific knowledge (not generic appliance repair).</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>What breaks on commercial pizza ovens, service patterns by category</h2>
    <p><b>Conveyor ovens</b> (Lincoln, Middleby Marshall): belt tension wears from continuous operation; burner ignitor degrades from high-cycle firing; thermostat drifts over 3–5 year service windows; air-flow sensor (signature Lincoln Impinger + Middleby Marshall WOW technology) malfunctions cause cook-consistency problems. Belt-replacement service is the most common conveyor call.</p>
    <p><b>Deck ovens</b> (Bakers Pride, Blodgett, Marsal): deck thermocouple fails from thermal cycling at 700–900°F deck temperatures; gas valve sticks or modulates poorly; burner ignitor wears; door hinge and refractory lining wear. Pizza stone replacement when decks crack from thermal cycling, typical 5–8 year deck lifespan in high-volume operation.</p>
    <p><b>Wood-fired ovens</b> (Wood Stone, Forno Bravo): flame-impingement calibration drifts on hybrid wood-plus-gas models; oven-door thermocouple and seal wear; wood-loading mechanism wear on models with automated wood feed; refractory lining inspection and maintenance; chimney/venting compliance with LADBS requirements. Wood-fired service requires specific training, not all competitor LA appliance service providers handle wood-fired work.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>California gas compliance, CARB, LADBS for commercial pizza ovens</h2>
    <p>Commercial gas pizza ovens in California require specific licensing and compliance framework. BHGS #A49573 license covers commercial appliance-repair service; CARB (California Air Resources Board) emissions compliance applies to commercial cooking equipment under Title 20; LADBS (Los Angeles Department of Building and Safety) permits are required for most commercial install and venting work. Our techs carry BHGS #A49573 licensing, CARB compliance documentation, and LADBS coordination experience.</p>
    <p>Wood-fired pizza ovens have additional venting compliance considerations. LADBS requires specific chimney/hood configurations for wood-burning commercial cooking equipment, and certain LA-County jurisdictions have additional air-quality restrictions on wood-fired cooking operations. CARB Title 20 standards on commercial cooking equipment emissions apply to wood-fired installations. Our work on LA wood-fired pizza ovens integrates the compliance framework with the actual equipment service.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Commercial pizza oven repair cost in LA</h2>
    <p>$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</p>
    <table class="price-table"><thead><tr><th>Repair category</th><th>Typical range (parts + labor)</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody><tr><td>Door gasket / hinge service</td><td>$180–$320</td></tr><tr><td>Thermostat replacement</td><td>$200–$340</td></tr><tr><td>Deck thermocouple (Bakers Pride, Blodgett, Marsal)</td><td>$220–$380</td></tr><tr><td>Burner ignitor assembly</td><td>$240–$400</td></tr><tr><td>Gas valve replacement</td><td>$280–$480</td></tr><tr><td>Air-flow sensor (conveyor)</td><td>$280–$460</td></tr><tr><td>Conveyor belt service (Lincoln / Middleby Marshall)</td><td>$320–$560</td></tr><tr><td>Wood-fired flame-impingement calibration</td><td>$320–$560</td></tr><tr><td>Pizza stone replacement (Blodgett 1048/1060)</td><td>$380–$680</td></tr><tr><td>Full burner refurbish</td><td>$500–$820</td></tr><tr><td>Control board replacement</td><td>$650–$1,200</td></tr></tbody></table>
    <p class="small">Most pizza oven calls land $350–$750 parts-and-labor. Deck oven, conveyor belt, and wood-fired specialty jobs run at the higher end.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related commercial pizza oven brand pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/middleby-marshall-pizza-oven-repair/"><b>Middleby Marshall pizza oven repair</b></a>, chain pizza OEM (Domino's, Pizza Hut, Papa John's, Little Caesars); PS + WOW conveyor</li>
